<subSubSection id="CABA3A9EFF822421FF621886FA199E37" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="821F6915FF822421FF621886FD239CA3" blockId="2.[151,685,436,460]" box="[151,685,436,460]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
<typeStatus id="5D1BD7B7FF822421FF621886FF479CA3" box="[151,201,436,460]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="45A01296FF822421FED31886FD239CA3" authority="(Schott, 1917)" baseAuthorityName="Schott" baseAuthorityYear="1917" box="[294,685,436,460]" class="Collembola" family="Entomobryidae" genus="Acanthocyrtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosus">
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FED31886FD989CA4" box="[294,534,436,460]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Acanthocyrtus spinosus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E63114E4FF822421FDD11886FD289CA3" author="Schott, H." box="[548,678,436,460]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" pagination="1 - 60" refId="ref9835" refString="Schott, H. (1917) Results of Dr. E. Mjoberg's Swedish Scientific Expeditions to Australia 1910 - 1913. N ° 15, Collembola. Arkiv for Zoologi, 11 (8), 1 - 60, 4 pl. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 1497" type="journal article" year="1917">Schött, 1917</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="821F6915FF822421FF6218C8FA199E37" blockId="2.[151,1437,506,856]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
These characters are shared by all 
<taxonomicName id="45A01296FF822421FDEC18C8FC9C9F7B" box="[537,786,506,532]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FDEC18C8FD359F7B" box="[537,699,506,532]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Acanthocyrtus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
so are not repeated in the species descriptions following: Tergal mac heavily ciliate apically, strongly or lightly foot-shaped or acuminate; smooth mic apically ramificate or not (
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF822421FF1C1B70FEA59F33" box="[233,299,578,604]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,2002,2026]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,813,1978]" captionTargetId="figure-272@1.[170,1418,813,1978]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Symbols used in the chaetotaxy descriptions of Acanthocyrtus species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410900/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Eyes 8+8 (
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF822421FE491B70FD9C9F33" box="[444,530,578,604]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1788,1812]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,181,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[151,1436,181,1764]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3A–F. Acanthocyrtus necropolitanus sp. nov., antennae and dorsal head; A, apex of left Ant IV (dorsal view); B, Ant III distally (lateral view); C, chaetotaxy (mac and elongated sens) of left Ant III–I (dorsal view, from left to right), respectively; D, chaetotaxy of clypeus and prelabrum; E, labral papillae (ventral view); F, head dorsal chaetotaxy and eyes (dorsal view, left side)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412858/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Figs 3F</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF822421FDBC1B70FDE19F33" box="[585,623,578,604]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[256,1332,181,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[256,1332,181,1869]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9A–F. Acanthocyrtus pallidus sp. nov., antennae and head; A, chaetotaxy (mac and elongated sens) of left Ant III–I (dorsal view, from left to right), respectively; B, chaetotaxy of clypeus (dorsal view); C, labral papillae (ventral view); D, head dorsal chaetotaxy and eyes (dorsal view, left side); E, labial papillae E (ventral view, right side); F, complete postlabial chaetotaxy (ventral view, right side)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410957/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">9D</figureCitation>
). Four prelabral chaetae smooth (
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF822421FC131B70FBCF9F33" box="[998,1089,578,604]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1788,1812]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,181,1764]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[151,1436,181,1764]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3A–F. Acanthocyrtus necropolitanus sp. nov., antennae and dorsal head; A, apex of left Ant IV (dorsal view); B, Ant III distally (lateral view); C, chaetotaxy (mac and elongated sens) of left Ant III–I (dorsal view, from left to right), respectively; D, chaetotaxy of clypeus and prelabrum; E, labral papillae (ventral view); F, head dorsal chaetotaxy and eyes (dorsal view, left side)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412858/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
); labral formula with 4 (
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FAA11B70FA029F33" bold="true" box="[1364,1420,578,604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">a1–2</emphasis>
), 5 (
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FF4D1B54FF779FEF" bold="true" box="[184,249,614,640]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">m0–2</emphasis>
), 5 (
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FEC61B54FEE39FEF" bold="true" box="[307,365,614,640]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">p0–2</emphasis>
) smooth chaetae. Labial palp with five main papillae (A–E) plus one hypostomal papilla (H) with 0, 5, 0, 4, 3 (
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FE961BB8FEF09FCB" bold="true" box="[355,382,650,676]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">e6</emphasis>
absent), 2 guard appendages, respectively. Sublobal plate with 4 smooth appendages, 3 inner subquals and 1 minute distally (
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF822421FDF31B9CFDEE9FA7" box="[518,608,686,712]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1491,1515]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,464,1468]" captionTargetId="figure-216@5.[151,1436,453,1468]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4A–D. Acanthocyrtus necropolitanus sp. nov., ventral head (right side); A, labial papillae E (right side); B, maxillary palp and sublobal plate (right side); C, basomedian and basolateral labial fields and proximal chaetae; D, complete postlabial chaetotaxy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410921/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Labium with 5 proximal chaetae smooth and subequals in length (
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF822421FA9A1B9CFF329F83" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1491,1515]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,464,1468]" captionTargetId="figure-216@5.[151,1436,453,1468]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4A–D. Acanthocyrtus necropolitanus sp. nov., ventral head (right side); A, labial papillae E (right side); B, maxillary palp and sublobal plate (right side); C, basomedian and basolateral labial fields and proximal chaetae; D, complete postlabial chaetotaxy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410921/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Basolateral and basomedian labial field with chaetae 
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FCD91BE0FCEA9F83" bold="true" box="[812,868,722,748]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">a1–5</emphasis>
smooth (
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF822421FC3A1BE0FBA79F83" box="[975,1065,722,748]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1491,1515]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,464,1468]" captionTargetId="figure-216@5.[151,1436,453,1468]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4A–D. Acanthocyrtus necropolitanus sp. nov., ventral head (right side); A, labial papillae E (right side); B, maxillary palp and sublobal plate (right side); C, basomedian and basolateral labial fields and proximal chaetae; D, complete postlabial chaetotaxy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410921/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Th II–Abd 
<collectionCode id="E4B1F1D0FF822421FB481BE0FB5F9F83" box="[1213,1233,722,748]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="2" pageNumber="343" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
with ms and sens formula 1, 0| 1, 0, 1, 0, 0 and 2, 2 | 1, 2, 2, +, 3, respectively (
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF822421FCC21BC4FCF39E7E" box="[823,893,758,785]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,453,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-169@6.[151,1436,453,1877]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5A–C. Acanthocyrtus necropolitanus sp. nov., dorsal chaetotaxy (left side); A, Th II–III; B, Abd I–III; C, Abd IV–V." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410929/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Figs 5</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF822421FC471BC4FC5F9E7F" box="[946,977,758,784]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[151,250,2010,2034]" captionTargetBox="[169,1420,597,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-256@11.[167,1420,597,1986]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10A–C. Acanthocyrtus pallidus sp. nov., dorsal chaetotaxy (left side); A, Th II–III; B, Abd I–III; C, Abd IV–V." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410961" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410961/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">10</figureCitation>
); Abd II–IV bothriotrichal formula 2 (
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FA8C1BC4FA1B9E7F" bold="true" box="[1401,1429,758,784]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">a5</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FF621A28FF339E5B" bold="true" box="[151,189,794,820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">m2</emphasis>
), 3 (
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FF041A28FE839E5B" bold="true" box="[241,269,794,820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">a5</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FEEF1A28FECE9E5B" bold="true" box="[282,320,794,820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">m2</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FEB81A28FEFC9E5B" bold="true" box="[333,370,794,820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">m5</emphasis>
), 2 (
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FE521A28FE499E5B" bold="true" box="[423,455,794,820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
<collectionCode id="E4B1F1D0FF822421FE521A28FE349E5B" box="[423,442,794,820]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">T</collectionCode>
2
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B0D4B507FF822421FE201A28FE7B9E5B" bold="true" box="[469,501,794,820]" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">
<collectionCode id="E4B1F1D0FF822421FE201A28FE669E5B" box="[469,488,794,820]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">T</collectionCode>
4
</emphasis>
) (
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF822421FDF81A28FDDD9E5A" box="[525,595,794,821]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1900,1924]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,453,1877]" captionTargetId="figure-169@6.[151,1436,453,1877]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5A–C. Acanthocyrtus necropolitanus sp. nov., dorsal chaetotaxy (left side); A, Th II–III; B, Abd I–III; C, Abd IV–V." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410929/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Figs 5</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF822421FD7D1A28FD299E5B" box="[648,679,794,820]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="11.[151,250,2010,2034]" captionTargetBox="[169,1420,597,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-256@11.[167,1420,597,1986]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 10A–C. Acanthocyrtus pallidus sp. nov., dorsal chaetotaxy (left side); A, Th II–III; B, Abd I–III; C, Abd IV–V." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410961" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410961/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">10</figureCitation>
); bothriotricha with accessory lance-shaped chaetae (
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF822421FB0C1A28FAB49E5B" box="[1273,1338,794,820]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,2002,2026]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,813,1978]" captionTargetId="figure-272@1.[170,1418,813,1978]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Symbols used in the chaetotaxy descriptions of Acanthocyrtus species." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410900/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Mucro bidentate, apical tooth subequal to proximal tooth, basal spine surpassing the apex of the proximal tooth (
<figureCitation id="1A9B7590FF822421FAC61A0CFA049E37" box="[1331,1418,830,856]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1378,1402]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,186,1347]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[151,1436,181,1354]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7A–E. Acanthocyrtus necropolitanus sp. nov., abdominal appendages; A, collophore (lateral view); B, distal manubrium (ventral view); C, manubrial plate (dorsal view), arrow indicates chaeta present or absent; D, dens spines chaetotaxy (dorsal view), E, distal dens and mucro (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410948/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="343">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
